# Angular distance matrix for orientation vectors

This function computes and returns the distance matrix computed by using
the Cosine similarity to compute the distances between the rows of a
data matrix.

## Usage

``` r
# S3 method for class 'Vec3'
dist(x, ...)

# S3 method for class 'Line'
dist(x, ...)

# S3 method for class 'Ray'
dist(x, ...)

# S3 method for class 'Plane'
dist(x, ...)

# S3 method for class 'Pair'
dist(x, ...)
```

## Arguments

- x:

  object of class `"Vec3"`, `"Line"`, `"Ray"`, `"Plane"`, `"Pair"`, or
  `"Fault"`, where the rows are the observations and the columns are the
  coordinates.

- ...:

  optional parameters passed to
  [`stats::as.dist()`](https://rdrr.io/r/stats/dist.html)

## Value

distance matrix

## Examples

set.seed(20250411)
